          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          UAE dismissed
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/uae-sudan-delegates-icj-hearing-the-hague.png" alt="Delegation members from the United Arab Emirates and Sudan stand at the start of a hearing before the International Court of Justice in The Hague" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Delegation members from the United Arab Emirates and Sudan stand at the start of a hearing before the International Court of Justice in The Hague. Credits: Remko de Waal/ANP/AFP/Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           The International Court of Justice (ICJ) ruled it <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-spotlight-h1-4-does-not-have-jurisdiction" target="_blank">does not have jurisdiction</a> to hear Sudan‚Äôs case against the United Arab Emirates (UAE). Sudan accused the UAE of violating the Genocide Convention by providing weapons to the paramilitary Rapid Support Forces (RSF), which have been in an ongoing civil war with the Sudanese army for the last two years.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The UAE countered that it had a reservation when joining the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-spotlight-h1-5-un-genocide-convention" target="_blank">UN Genocide Convention</a> in 2005. The reservation prevents it from being sued by other states at the ICJ. The court conceded that it doesn‚Äôt have the authority to hear the case, but still expresses a deep concern over the ongoing violence and humanitarian crisis in Sudan, particularly in West Darfur. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The war has displaced many, caused famine in several regions, and led to many civilian casualties. The RSF reportedly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-spotlight-h1-6-attacked-port-sudan" target="_blank">attacked Port Sudan</a> for three consecutive days, targeting the airport, civilian infrastructure, and oil depots. The ICJ stresses that states are accountable for internationally wrongful deeds, even if they have jurisdictional reservations. 
         </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Currently, 153 states are party to the Genocide Convention, with 16 states inserting blanket reservations, including the UAE.
         </p>
        
        </mj-text>
