          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Germany elects chancellor</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: Bundestag confirmed Friedrich Merz as Germany's chancellor in a successful second vote. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Friedrich Merz officially became Germany‚Äôs chancellor <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-spotlight-h2-7-following-a-dramatic-first-vote" target="_blank">following a dramatic first vote</a> in the Bundestag, where he missed the required majority. In the first round, Merz fell six votes short of the required 316 votes. It was the first time an incoming chancellor failed to secure a majority in the first round after triumphing in an election.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Yet, a few hours later, he clinched the second round with 325 votes. The first vote was a personal setback for Merz as he expected an easy win, especially since the center-right CDU party and left-wing SPD party together held 328 seats. There was some dissent within the CDU and SPD despite the coalition being agreed upon by 84% of the party base. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Meanwhile, opposition parties, including the far-right party, were calling for renewed elections. Losing the first round shows he is still a relatively unpopular choice for the position. His confirmation ends <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-spotlight-h2-8-months-of-political-gridlock" target="_blank">months of political gridlock</a>, but he faces significant economic and political challenges.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
