      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáªüá¶ Vatican City - Pope conclave starts.</strong> This evening, 133 cardinals will meet in the Sistine Chapel to elect the 267th pope. They need a two-thirds majority to decide, and the voting will continue until the majority is achieved. White smoke from the chimney to the right of St Peter's Basilica will signal the selection of the next Pope (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-worldwide-11-the-conclave-process" target="_blank">the conclave process</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá´üá∑ France - Courting US scientists.</strong> France and the EU plan to launch an incentives package worth $567M to US-based scientists affected by Donald Trump‚Äôs academic crackdowns. The initiatives aim to attract health, climate, and AI experts, despite Europe‚Äôs historic funding and salary disadvantages compared to the US (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-worldwide-12-science-refugees" target="_blank">science refugees</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá∏üáæ Syria - Interim president visits Europe.</strong> French President Emmanuel Macron will host Syrian leader Ahmed al-Sharaa in Paris. Macron supports a democratic Syria, but there are ongoing concerns over recent sectarian violence. Al-Sharaa aims to lift sanctions on Syria (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-worldwide-13-trip-to-paris" target="_blank">trip to Paris</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáÆüá≥ India - Mock war drills.</strong> Due to tensions with Pakistan, India is conducting its first air raid mock drills since 1971 at 250 locations nationwide in the wake of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-worldwide-14-operation-sindoor" target="_blank">Operation Sindoor</a>. The drills involve air raid sirens, communication system tests, and civil defense training. Civilians will practice blackout measures, evacuations, and emergency responses to prepare for the worst-case scenario (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-worldwide-15-raising-tensions" target="_blank">raising tensions</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáßüá¨ Bulgaria - Spies to be sentenced.</strong> 
           A ring of Bulgarian spies led by Orlin Roussev, tied to Russia, will be convicted in a British court. The spy ring was hired to conduct espionage on targets across the UK and Europe (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-7-may-25-worldwide-16-the-story" target="_blank">the story</a>).
          </p>
          
        </mj-text>
